OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F358A1777378266
OL,3,CKendal's County Hall to be sold,
OL,4,CWestmorland and Furness Cabinet decides
OL,6,FCllr Andrew Jarvis, Deputy Leader and
OL,7,FCabinet Member for Finance, argues
OL,8,Frationalising the large number of
OL,9,Fbuildings inherited when four councils
OL,10,Fcombined to form Westmorland and
OL,11,FFurness Council three years ago would
OL,12,Fdeliver value for money.
OL,14,FHe said: "We know County Hall is part
OL,15,Fof Kendal's story, and we understand
OL,16,Fpeople will feel strongly about what
OL,17,Fhappens next. We believe it can have a
OL,18,Fbright and useful future, and also
OL,19,Fremain an important part of the town's
OL,20,Fidentity and architecture.
OL,26,@vD@JOU
